context capital management – absolute return credit opportunities skip to content   context capital management llc about – context capital management skip to content about context capital   context capital management llc is an secregistered alternative asset management firm based in la jolla california and jupiter florida our firm looks for asymmetric return profiles opportunities where downside risk is protected and upside can be exploited specifically we specialize in fixed income and relativevalue strategies with a focus on eventdriven credit trades trades are most typically constructed with long convertible andor corporate bonds and short common stock positions   we strive to achieve consistent absolute rates of return with an emphasis on the preservation of capital via rigorous risk management and a diversified portfolio context pursues a number of synergistic investment strategies with diverse themes and return drivers once it identifies investment opportunities it establishes trades to isolate asymmetric return distributions this tailored approach to investing allows context to also construct bespoke funds or managed accounts in consultation with its clients   our approach – context capital management skip to content our approach universe the global convertible bond convertible preferred and mandatory universe has a market capitalization of nearly b with approximately  of the universe us based companies mrrosen mr fertig and mr carnegie each have extensive experience managing portfolios of these securities from issuers in the us emea japan and asia new issuance in the sector have been robust over the years across many different economic cycles as companies of all sizes find it advantageous to issue new bonds when volatility in the equity markets is elevated when interest rates are high or when fast growing smaller companies need to finance their growth research fundamental and quantitative analysis leverage extensive network of business and industry contacts leverage internal knowledge of specific companies and industries maintain active dialogue with portfolio company management portfolio bottomup selection process with adherence to diversification mandate crossstrategy idea generation and trade construction topdown capital allocation based on relative value controls rigorous risk management process diversification and concentration limits limited use of leverage strict legal and compliance standards      our team – context capital management skip to content our team michael s rosen cfa cochairman chief executive officer and cofounder is widely recognized for his expertise in managing convertible securities mr rosen was the coprincipal owner of rochester capital advisors lp and fmc inc the two investment advisers to the rochester funds a mutual fund company specializing in the management of convertible securities and highyield municipal bonds from inception in  to the sale of those funds to oppenheimer funds inc in january  assets under management grew to  billion currently assets managed by the rochester division total more than  billion at the time of the sale the convertible securities fund managed by mr rosen had the best fiveyear performance as ranked by lipper analytical from  to  mr rosen served as a portfolio manager and president of the rochester division of oppenheimer funds inc businessweek named mr rosen the “best bond fund manager” in  mr rosen has been on the board of trustees for the university of rochester since  where he also serves on the investment and development committees mr rosen is cofounder director and chairman of reality shares inc mr rosen was a director of entravision nyse – evc from  –  during  he served on the audit committee and the compensation committee past director positions also include global locate inc  –  danskin inc  –  and palmer r chitester fund  –  he received a ba degree in economics and an mba in finance and marketing from the university of rochester in  and  respectively mr rosen is also a chartered financial analyst william d fertig cochairman chief investment officer and cofounder has been actively involved in virtually all aspects of the us convertible high yield and equity markets for the first nine years of his career mr fertig was a proprietary trader for ef hutton and credit suisse mr fertig headed convertible sales at credit suisse and drexel burnham lambert in  mr fertig spearheaded mcmahan securities’ entry into the brokerage business focusing exclusively on convertible and derivative securities as managing director he oversaw the sales and trading efforts and served on the executive and risk management committees under mr fertig’s direction mcmahan securities grew to be one of the nation’s largest independent convertible and derivative securities dealers mr fertig has been involved in more than one hundred corporate underwritings and debt restructurings mr fertig has been a member of the key energy services board of directors since  he chairs the nominating  corporate governance committee and sits on the compensation committee and executive committee since june of  mr fertig has been a trustee for proshares and profunds the world’s largest provider of leveraged and inverse funds mr fertig received a bs with high honors in economics from allegheny college and was elected to phi beta kappa he received his mba with a concentration in finance from new york university’s stern school in  charles carnegie cfa joined context as a managing partner and portfolio manager in november  this is mr carnegies second goaround with the context team as he began his career here mr carnegie is coming from hutchin hill capital management where he was a senior credit analyst and trader focused on credit and relative value opportunities including convertible high yield and distressed corporate bonds and capital structure arbitrage previously mr carnegie worked at graham capital management a large macro focused hedge fund where he worked in a simi